the judges decision was delivered by sir frederick lawton at the 
end of a 3hour tv film of the testimony titled waldheim a 
commission of inquiry 
we have not been asked to decide whether dr waldheim is or is 
not guilty of a crime still less has it been our function to pass a 
moral judgement upon him said the 76yearold former lord justice 
of britains appeal court 
a person does not commit a war crime merely because he knows 
others have committed such crimes nor because he worked with or 
alongside those who committed them lawton said 
his colleagues were shirley hufstedler a former circuit judge 
