<TEXT>
the navy has awarded a contract to a dutch firm 
to transport the damaged frigate uss samuel b roberts home from the 
persian gulf aboard a heavylift ship the service said monday 
the contract was awarded last week to wijsmuller transport of 
ijmuiden the netherlands and totals 1325 million said navy 
spokeswoman marge holtz 
it calls for the firm to use its semisubmersible heavylift 
ship mighty servant 2 to pick up and carry the roberts from 
dubai in the united arab emirates to bath maine where it is to be 
repaired at the bath iron works 
the guidedmissile frigate which is based at newport ri was 
badly ripped by an underwater mine on april 14 shortly after 
completing a convoy operation for a reflagged kuwaiti tanker navy 
officials have said the roberts almost certainly would have sunk had 
it not been for the performance of its crew of roughly 200 
the navy announced last month it had solicited bids from maritime 
operators of heavylift ships to carry the roberts home saying such 
a move would be preferable to performing extensive repairs in dubai 
and then towing it 
the mighty servant 2 one of about two dozen such heavylift 
ships in operation measures 558 feet long and 132 feet wide it is 
designed to sink underneath its cargo and then deballast or 
rise up bringing its cargo out of the water 
such ships are used frequently to handle large oil derricks the 
mighty servant 2 can cruise at about 14 knots when underway 
according to the navy there is only one such ship in the us 
fleet and it is assigned to the military sealift command and 
deployed with a wartime readiness force at diego garcia in the 
indian ocean 
it would be prohibitively expensive to unload that vessel and 
there are no other usflag ships of this type available said 
ms holtz thats why we went to a foreign contractor 
the spokeswoman declined to discuss the schedule for moving the 
roberts citing security concerns last month however the navy 
said it hoped the voyage could begin before the end of june 
with the exception of approximately 10 crewmen who will ride 
the heavylift ship the crew of the uss roberts will fly to their 
home port of newport ri when their ship departs for the united 
states the navy said at the time 
</TEXT>
