<TEXT>
a san josebound american airlines jet 
carrying 105 people returned safely to los angeles international 
airport on monday after fuel leaked from a wing because a fuel cap 
didnt work officials said 
american flight 2223 a boeing 737 was loaded with 16000 pounds 
of fuel when it took off at 1037 am the pilot returned to los 
angeles declaring an emergency said elly brekke a spokeswoman for 
the federal aviation administration 
an air traffic controller advised the pilot that fuel was 
venting from the right wing she said 
with firefighters standing by jetliner landed safely at 1057 
am and the passengers and crew left without having to use 
emergency chutes ms brekke said 
our maintenance people have examined the plane and determined 
that a locking tab on a filler cap on the upper right wing was not 
functioning steve mcgregor an american airlines spokesman in 
fort worth texas said by telephone there was indeed a fuel 
leak 
mcgregor said the passengers were placed on american flight 1091 
which left los angeles for san jose at 1139 am 
he said the plane with the malfunctioning filler cap was expected 
to be back in service later in the day 
