a handmade rug two years in the design and 
making and purchased by an anonymous donor for 49625 at the 
request of nancy reagan has been installed in the oval office of 
the white house it was announced monday 
the allwool ovalshaped rug measures 31 feet 2 inches by 23 
feet 9 inches and weighs more than 375 pounds white house spokesman 
marlin fitzwater said 
with a 4foot circular presidential seal at its center the rug 
is decorated with 40 customdyed colors the predominant color is 
peach or coral the outer border 18 inches wide is decorated with 
green olive leaves and garlands 
the rug was installed while president reagan was at the moscow 
summit it replaced a specially designed oval rug with turquoise 
rosettes on a pale gold background that was installed in 1976 the 
old rug will be put in storage fitzwater said 
he said the reagans wanted to leave an asset to the white house 
and they felt this would be an attractive asset 
he said the first lady worked with the white house curator and 
white house historical association to design the rug and get a 
donor who wished not to be identified 
the rug was made in auburn maine for the stark carpet corp of 
new york city 
