the court agreed to decide whether railroads may require all 
employees involved in serious accidents to submit to drug testing 
the court will review an appeals court decision that struck down as 
an unconstitution invasion of privacy the federal regulations 
requiring mandatory testing of railroad employees the case is 
bunley vs railway labor executives association 871555 
</TEXT>
