burial the reason then was the large and grieving crowds that 
slowed the train carrying his coffin from new york after a service 
in st patricks cathedral the funeral was four hours late and in 
the darkness children held lighted candles 
now the late hour was set to accommodate close friends and others 
who wanted to share the memory with his family 
robert kennedy then a senator from new york and running for the 
democratic presidential nomination was fatally shot in los angeles 
shortly after midnight on june 5 1968 following a brief speech at 
a hotel to 2000 campaign supporters who were celebrating his 
california primary victory the previous evening he died the 
following day 
