<TEXT>
efforts to unite europe have been alive 
for centuries napoleon and hitler tried it by force 
not until after the devastation of world war ii did a peaceful 
approach catch on 
jean monnet a french economist and robert schuman a french 
foreign minister are considered the fathers of the european coal 
and steel community a forerunner of todays european economic 
community or common market 
the community celebrates its birthday each year on may 9 the 
date in 1950 on which schuman formally proposed pooling the coal and 
steel industries of france and west germany and setting up a 
european common market in coal a little less than seven years later 
the eec was born 
these are some other famous figures in eec history 
paulhenri spaak a belgian statesman engineered the socalled 
spaak report which drew up a blueprint for developing a european 
union the report was adopted on may 29 1956 and led directly to 
the treaty of rome that created the eec on march 25 1957 
etienne davignon a belgian member of the eec commission in the 
early 1980s he masterminded the davignon plan for spending billions 
of dollars to revitalize europes most basic industry steel 
jacques delors a frenchman and current president of the eec 
commission he is credited with leading the community into perhaps 
its most dynamic phase of commerical and monetary integration 
