<TEXT>
joe has been born again 
my longtime baitcastin buddy was standing hip deep in the 
little rapids whipping bits of fur and feather under the willow 
branches overhanging a quiet pool 
hes become a fly fisherman 
fly fishing long has been considered an elite level of angling 
its highly effective not only for trout but for bass and a whole 
assortment of panfish 
heavyduty rigs also have been devised for ocean fish that tip 
the scale in three figures 
one caution fly fishing is not for everyone if you get past the 
beginner stage it becomes addictive if you catch a really good 
fish on a fly rod you never want to catch one any other way again 
joe warned me 
knowing that if you want to get started in fly fishing there 
are two ways go to a school or teach yourself there also is an 
assortment of books and videos to help 
there are some simple tips to start in fly fishing 
unlike baitcasting or spinfishing where the lure carries the 
line flyfishing uses the line to carry an almost weightless fly 
the fly is attached to a nearly invisible tippet which the fish 
cant see the rig allows the bit of fluff to settle gently on the 
water as if it fell off a branch just above the bank 
the line which can be either a sinking or floating line does 
most of the work whipping back and forth in a delicate arc carying 
the fly to the fish 
so buy a good line 
an average rod can cast a good line but the best of rods wont 
cast a cheap line properly 
lines are measured by weight based on the weight in grains for 
the first 30 feet of line after the front taper weights range from 
no 2 to no 13 
lines and rods should match each other to assure proper casting 
start with an 8foot 5 or 6weight rod from a reputable maker 
you can get a good quality graphite rod for 50 or less fiberglass 
rods cost about half that 
the ultimate rod is handmade of split bamboo but dont worry 
about one of those until you are good enough to really appreciate it 
as you get started a moderately priced reel is sufficient its 
sole function early in the learning process is to store line not in 
use 
read your books study your videos and practice practice 
practice 
remember youre not whipping a team of horses learn the basic 
movement of bringing the rod hand forward from the back cast before 
you break your wrist in the power stroke 
when youre ready to try your skill on fish go to a tackle shop 
that caters to fly fishermen for advice on flies the adage in fly 
fishing is match the hatch pick flies which resemble whatever 
insects are flitting around and falling into the water or hatching 
from the bottom of the area you plan to fish 
finally begin your fly fishing career where you have some room 
flies tangle in branches just as easily as crankbaits hang up in 
bushes pick a stream thats wadeable in hip boots 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

