fantastic onyx and luray foster said 
there are nearly 200 of these caves are one of the few natural 
resources that people regularly pay money to go and look at 
the american speleological society acca was founded to help 
protect those resources members are cavers who belong to local 
clubs or grottos across the country 
while caves can be spacious enough to hold large buildings inside 
them they also can be far too small for a human to worm through but 
can run for miles providing freeways through the rock for pollution 
cave protection is not just protecting a few pretty rock 
formations its protecting groundwater resources foster said 
people in karst areas of missouri arkansas tennessee and 
kentucky may be drinking their own sewage because they dont know 
how far and fast this stuff is moving 
karst is soluble rock slit with cracks fissures and passages 
bacteria industrial contaminents can move a long long way 
without being filtered out its the worst place you can possibily 
put anything because it mainlines it directly into the groundwater 
system 
we want to try foster said to stop the consequences of 
poor land use planning we have very beautiful mineral formations 
archaeological sites endangered species a wealth of resources down 
there that people think are insignificant because you dont see them 
every day theyre out of sight out of mind 
