<TEXT>
britains commercial banks heeding a signal from 
the bank of england raised their base lending rate monday by half a 
percentage point to 85 percent 
it was the second increase in the benchmark rate in less than a 
week and represents an aggressive move by the government to boost 
the sagging pound and counter inflationary pressures 
barclays banks plc midland bank plc and lloyds bank plc raised 
their rate effective immediately national westminster bank said it 
would raise its rate effective friday 
the bank of england signaled the increase by raising a key money 
market intervention rate of its own to 85 percent 
last thursday the central bank signaled a rise in the base rate 
to 8 percent from 75 percent after the pound dropped sharply on 
foreign exchange markets the increase was effective friday 
the foreign exchange market reacted calmly to the latest 
increase dealers said because a rate hike was widely anticipated 
it was going to happen sooner or later and it happened 
sooner one dealer said 
sterling rose to a session high 18060 just after the central 
banks move but settled back to 18035 slightly up from 18020 
during the morning 
corporate borrowers can obtain loans at 1 percentage point above 
the prevailing base rate 
