<DOCNO> AP880606-0283 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
makers of leadfree solder say their sales are 
rising as the nation nears a june 19 deadline for mandatory use of 
leadfree solder in homes under construction 
legislation passed by congress in 1986 severely limited lead in 
pipes solder or flux used in drinking water systems of new homes 
it gave states a grace period of two years to change construction 
codes to comply with the law 
the legislation also prohibits the housing and urban development 
department and the veterans administration from backing loans for 
newly built homes that have lead in the drinkingwater systems 
sales have been great said thomas bannos product manager 
for joining products at engelhard corp which makes silvabrite 100 
a leadfree solder that has half a percent silver 
especially in the last few months it has very dramatically 
picked up said bob rushmore vice president of sales and 
marketing for atlantabased taracorp inc which also makes a 
leadfree solder containing silver 
silver gives the solder a broader temperature range in which it 
is mushy and easy to work with 
among the companies that make leadfree or virtually leadfree 
solder are engelhard of edison nj taracorp of atlanta which 
sells taramet sterling jw harris co of cincinnati with 
staysafe bridgit bow solder products co and mc canfield and 
sons sister companies that sell water pure solder and water safe 
solder and oatey co of cleveland with safe flo silverbearing 
solder 
many of the companies also sell leadfree flux which is a 
jellylike substance that helps in the application of solder 
the law bans solder or flux with more than 02 percent lead and 
pipes and pipe fittings with more than 8 percent lead 
the environmental protection agency estimates as many as 40 
million americans may be exposed to what it considers excessive 
levels of lead in drinking water 
although lead has been used for centuries plumbing comes from 
the latin word for lead lead is a poison that in high enough 
concentrations can cause kidney and brain damage children are most 
at risk because their brains are still being formed 
the epa says drinking water accounts for about 10 to 20 percent 
of the lead consumption by children the majority comes from food 
dust and soil 
the lead problem is greatest in homes built before 1930 which 
often have lead pipes and in homes less than 5 years old in homes 
more than 5 years old any lead has usually become covered with a 
coating of lime 
lead is soft and can usually be scratched by a key or 
screwdriver however only an inspection can determine for sure if a 
plumbing system contains lead 
lead concentrations are highest in water that has been sitting in 
the pipes so people concerned about lead should let the water run 
for a moment when they turn on a faucet that has been off for a long 
time 
also hot water leaches more lead so only cold water should be 
used for cooking and preparing baby foods water softeners which 
also leach lead should be hooked up only to hot water since the hot 
water will not be used for drinking or food preparation 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880606-0284 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the supreme court agreed monday to decide 
whether federal workers locked in a dispute with the union 
representing them may sue in federal court 
the justices said they will review a ruling that limits federal 
employees in such instances to filing an unfair labor practices 
charge with the federal labor relations authority 
federal appeals courts have reached conflicting decisions on the 
issue 
in the case of efthimios karahalios a greek language instructor 
at the defense language institute in monterey calif the 9th us 
circuit court of appeals ruled he could not sue in federal court 
karahalios had worked for the institute for nearly 20 years when 
in 1976 he was promoted to the higher paying position of course 
developer 
another greek language instructor simon kuntelos filed a 
grievance with the national federation of federal employees which 
represents the institutes workers over karahalios promotion 
karahalios was not a member of the union but it represented him 
in collective bargaining kuntelos is a member of the union 
the union decided to arbitrate kuntelos grievance but did not 
tell karahalios about it after a hearing not attended by 
karahalios an arbitrator cleared the way for kuntelos in effect 
to get karahalios job 
karahalios objected to his demotion but the union refused to 
arbitrate on his behalf 
karahalios filed an unfair labor practice complaint with the 
federal labor relations authority but the union and the agency 
settled the case when the union agreed to state that it would not 
undertake similar acts in the future 
after objecting unsuccessfully to the settlement karahalios sued 
the union in federal court 
a federal trial judge ruled that the union had breached its duty 
to give karahalios fair representation although no damages were 
awarded the union was ordered to pay the legal fees that karahalios 
incurred in pursuing the lawsuit 
the appeals court threw out the judges ruling stating that 
congress intended the federal labor relations authority to be the 
sole forum for disputes between federal employees and their unions 
the reagan administration citing conflicting rulings in lower 
courts urged the justices to grant karahalios appeal but 
government lawyers argued that the appeals court ruling was correct 
the case is karahalios vs defense language institute 87636 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

